Text.string: I'll chat with ya later, Vault Hunter. Right now, you gotta rescue Alistair.
The team's waitin' for ya.
Alistair first. We'll talk after he's safe.
Welcome to Eden-6. As you can see, we've got ourselves a little zealot problem.
The Children of the Vault have descended on my planet like locusts, and there's only one cure for locusts: fire.
Eden-6 ain't been the same since the Calypsos murdered my father. But like they say, murder's a debt that must be paid in full.
I'm glad my father ain't alive to see me now, though I miss him dearly, Vault Hunter. Say your goodbyes when you can.
Let's give those bandits an unwanted mud bath at the night spa—kill 'em, is what I'm saying.
I spoke with your commanding officer, and we've reached an accord. You help me take back this planet, and I'll get you that Vault Key.

You know, if you hadn't come along when you did... well... I'd have been just fine. I'm a Jakobs, after all. Strong as a jabber and better lookin', too! Just a jest, Vault Hunter. I'm glad you're here.
What do you think of Clay? Is he the type to take the money and run, or is he around for the long haul?
My father trusted Clay. Not sure if I do, but when your back's against the wall, you ain't got much choice than to trust the man standing next to ya.
The Family Jewel is a ship that's been in my family for generations. It crashed in the Voracious Canopy some time ago.
Aurelia Hammerlock was born to be a CEO, and I ain't ashamed to admit it. The sky's the limit in this galaxy, if all you desire is money.
Those mercenaries I hired made for Pandora. If you run into 'em, you tell those crazy bastards I am eternally in their debt.
When you finally confront those Calypso devils, you tell 'em that long after their cult is in the mud, Jakobs Corporation'll still be on dry land.
I can't thank ya enough for what you've done. You'll always have a friend on Eden-6.
Me and Alistair are gonna tidy up around here. Putting bandits in mud has becoming our date night. Lotta date nights recently.
Been a while, Vault Hunter. As you can see, we've still got a zealot problem, but Clay, Alistair and myself are up to the task!

I've heard rumblings of an Eridian homeworld. Once the corporations get word, they're gonna descend on that planet. And when they're done, there won't just be no meat on the bone—the bone'll be pulverized. Ain't no more voracious beast in this galaxy than a corporation.
I spoke to your commanding officer, and all that's left to say is good luck. We'll be rooting for ya.
Well, those Calypso devils are gone for good. Too bad about your commanding officer, but war and sacrifice go hand-in-hand, I suppose.
You did it! You put that Tyreen Calypso in the mud! I'm proud of ya, Vault Hunter!
You seem to have a touch of the wanderlust!
My, oh, my! You've got more bloodlust than a saurian in heat!
You ever been in love, Vault Hunter?
How's Eden-6 treating ya? If you've got a... ahem, a swamp a brewin', take a dip in a waterfall! Just keep your eyes peeled for saurians.
My father hired Typhon DeLeon himself to come here, but the First Vault Hunter couldn't find our Vault. Ain't that somethin'?
Jakobs tried to sidestep the corporate war, but when the jabbers start flinging crap, even bystanders are bound to get some on their shoe.
Alistair and I met a few years back on a hunting expedition. My father set us up, truth be told. Despite being a Jakobs, I ain't much with a rifle—but Alistair can drop a saurian with a single shot.
Still alive, I see! Well, good! Hoping you stay that way!
Who taught you to shoot? Wish my father was alive to see you put those zealots in the mud.
If you get some time to yourself, you should visit the other Edens. They ain't all like this one.
I've never been to Pandora myself, but Alistair tells me... I shouldn't go.
A Vault Hunter on Eden-6... just what my father warned me of so long ago.
Alistair's rescuer, in the flesh.
There's the clever bastard who went toe-to-toe with the harpy and survived!
It's the hero of Reliance! That'll make the history books!
How's the Family Jewel looking?
Well, the Ambermire tried to put you in the mud, didn't it, Vault Hunter? Good to see you're still on dry land!
There's the gunslinger who put me back on the throne!
The hero of the galaxy in my presence! Well, let's catch up over a spread of genuine Jakobs firearms!
Feels like we ought not be idlin' about, and yet...
Idle hands, as they say.
Swamp ass. Always and forever.
Now where's that damn jabber...
[humming] I miss ya, mama.
Mind if I bend your ear for a tick?
If you're bored or broke, I've got something for ya.
Maybe you could help me whittle down my honey-do list.
Greetings, friend!
How goes it, Vault Hunter?
If it ain't my favorite gunslinger!
Well, if I ain't in the presence of a walking legend!
Do you and I have business, or is this just a “how the hell are ya doing”?
Howdy, sunshine!
Look who ain't sleeping one off.
Burnin' the midnight grog-oil, aren't we?
Good to see you! Especially with lighting that's a bit more amenable to your particular appearance.
Excellent choice in that there Jakobs firearm.
Ah, a Jakobs. I see you've got good taste.
Shall we find some trouble?
How'd you like to work for me?
I've got something for you, if your gun's willing.
I've got a remedy for that bored look in your eyes.
Vault Hunter! Just who I wanted to see.
You get stuck in the mud or something?
Still waiting for that task I sent ya on.
Can I count on ya to fulfill your obligations?
You gonna complete that task or shall I find another gunslinger?
Let me know when the deed is done.
So long!
Take care of yourself, Vault Hunter.
Until next time, I suppose.
Holler if you need me.
Keep your gun oiled, Vault Hunter.
Time to pour on the fire, I suppose.
Give the jabbers my regards.
Tell the saurians I'll see them soon.
Try to stay out of the mud, ya hear?
Until next time, gunslinger.
